","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g water, plus extra for soaking skewers"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g skinless chicken thighs, cut into pieces (2-3 cm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"70 g red onion"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ stalk fresh lemongrass, white part only, cut into thin slices (optional)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 cm cube fresh ginger, peeled"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tsp lime juice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 garlic clove"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 pinches salt, to taste, plus extra to season"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 pinches freshly ground black pepper, to taste, plus extra to season"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g basmati rice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"400 g coconut milk"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 tbsp light olive oil, for frying"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portions","563 kJ \/ 134 kcal","7.5 g","6 g","9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","Some coconut milk products can be made using equipment that has come into contact with dairy products. If dairy allergies are a concern for you, be sure to check the label of your coconut milk or make your own (please refer to the Choc-mint milk recipe on this recipe chip).","For younger children, use smaller skewers or cut off the sharp ends of full-size skewers.","For adults, serve with your favourite chilli sauce.","Recipe contributed by Louise Keats, from her book <em>Something for Everyone<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","14 portions"]}